author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: Falcons pick up fourth win in five games, hammer Apalachee
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 8: Surprises abound in wild night of prep football VIDEO: Rabun County routs Union County in top 10 showdown, 49-3 
FLOWERY BRANCH — Flowery Branch football keeps playing its way into form. The Falcons notched their fourth win in five games on Friday with a 41-6 victory over Apalachee in Flowery Branch. 
The win helped keep the Falcons (5-3, 4-3 Region 8- ) in contention for a playoff spot in Region 8- and showed off the Branch's defensive prowess. 
Apalachee (0-7, 0-6) managed just 150 total yards on the night -- led by 89 yards rushing and a touchdown from Stephen Massillon. It was far from enough to derail the Falcons, however. 
Kory Graham passed for two touchdowns on five completions, finishing with 105 yards through the air. His first score went for 66 yards to receiver Cortez Davis. Trey Wilcoxson also scored three touchdowns while rushing for 86 yards on 15 carries to help pace the Falcons. 
Flowery Branch took a 21-6 halftime advantage and then blew the game open with 20 unaswered points in the third quarter. 
The Falcons will take a bye next week before looking to maintain their momentum on Oct. 30 against Salem. 
Apalachee will look to bounce back next week against Heritage. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Flowery Branch football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
